<subSubSection id="B95D58B6364CC611F7FF3D5A95D6C3E5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph id="1DFB438AE25423F0CDCCDE8E3A96C41D" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1383FE0F0BFBCE8BC92518684A32CEA1" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Female (
<figureCitation id="264B768ABF4124DD2E9F66100751BA36" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Length. 7.0 mm. Similar to male except for penultimate metasomal segment and sheath black, and genitalic characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BDC778ADE30F0E2BF50C8A80D807BA78" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="male">
<paragraph id="55A5944C289E38CC8436507258FE7858" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Male.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D4C02DE1471B6B1D942AA4EF2951F98" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
(
<figureCitation id="96BEFDA576B62DFA77B8A7A790EC5450" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Length. 5.0-8.0 mm. Antenna black, antennomeres 9-16 and sometimes 17 white. Head white with vertex and gena black, black extending anteriorly as V-shaped mark in front of ocelli; broad black median stripe on clypeus (
<figureCitation id="2C0E978AD127775C90B42AFA8C0A9AC9" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Orthogonalys brevis, male paratype. 4 Head, front view. 5 Head, dorsal view. 6 Apex of abdomen and genitalia, lateral view. 7 Genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11358" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
). Mesosoma pale orange. Legs pale orange with hind tibia and tarsus darker to black. Wings hyaline, veins brown, costa more orange toward base; stigma brown to orange with anterior margin black. Genitalia brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9905B71B18B24F2FD3C827A98192FB2C" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<pageBreakToken id="74A23E33F988B15C6F827568DDB691E7" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" start="start">Antenna</pageBreakToken>
with 28 antennomeres. Head from above slightly concave behind, distance behind eyes about 0.7
<normalizedToken id="2AB4D357EDC151F6514F84781DFBB291" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye length (
<figureCitation id="1C8CC62F4453938CE1ADF3A415614CB0" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Orthogonalys brevis, male paratype. 4 Head, front view. 5 Head, dorsal view. 6 Apex of abdomen and genitalia, lateral view. 7 Genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11358" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Metascutellum broader than long, anterior breadth about 1.3
<normalizedToken id="934B61B1EC47FACF61E9344373A04EE1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
medial length; metascutellum about 2.0
<normalizedToken id="7B1FCB5301D0924283A5F262198C0F67" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long (
<figureCitation id="C29D98CB73BAF44159B7CC881FC04B93" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Dorsum of mesosoma shiny, with widely spaced small punctures farther apart than 2-3
<normalizedToken id="83BD606781EC4C78844C06F6C90B8D1D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
puncture diameters. Propodeum coarsely reticulate (
<figureCitation id="6329B6FB4970A0CF99D724B091A03C7C" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Orthogonalys brevis. 1 Female paratype, lateral view. 2 Male paratype, lateral view. 3 Mesosoma and metasoma, male, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11357" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia with paramere short, 1.6
<normalizedToken id="58DD51BCCDC3B905CABD2564D60FD22F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
broader than long, broadly rounded at apex, about 0.5
<normalizedToken id="3FD3CACEDC84207D275BCDB64C247954" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of gonostipes (
<figureCitation id="78A1D05F5A72A75175DF69B9D95E8F12" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Orthogonalys brevis, male paratype. 4 Head, front view. 5 Head, dorsal view. 6 Apex of abdomen and genitalia, lateral view. 7 Genitalia, dorsal view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11358" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Figs 6, 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
